<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T005 AI Workflow Snapshot</title><style>@page{margin:.6in}body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.45;color:#111827;max-width:8.1in;margin:0 auto;background:#fff}h1{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;padding:16px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:22pt;margin:0 0 14px}h2{color:#0f172a;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px;margin:18px 0 8px;font-size:15pt}p{margin:8px 0 12px}ul{margin:8px 0 14px 24px}li{margin:4px 0}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;table-layout:fixed;margin:10px 0 16px}th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 9px;vertical-align:top;word-wrap:break-word}th{background:#dbeafe;color:#0f172a;text-align:left}.meta{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #dbe3ec;border-radius:10px;padding:10px 12px}.visual{text-align:center;margin:12px 0 16px}.visual img{width:100%;max-width:7.15in;height:auto;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:10px}.note{background:#eff6ff;border-left:6px solid #0ea5e9;padding:10px 12px;margin:10px 0;border-radius:6px}.small{font-size:9pt;color:#475569;border-top:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding-top:8px;margin-top:18px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - AI Workflow Snapshot</h1><p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T005<br><b>Package:</b> AI Workflow Snapshot<br><b>Scenario:</b> Repeated admin work to owner dashboard lite</p><div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-ai-proof.svg" alt="AI workflow visual"></div><h2>Customer input received</h2><ul><li>Repeated tasks: reply to leads, chase missing info, build quote drafts, follow up after delivery.</li><li>Tools used: Gmail, Google Drive, Google Forms, Google Sheets.</li><li>Pain point: every customer request starts from scratch.</li><li>Goal: create a simple AI-assisted workflow without building a full app.</li></ul><h2>Workflow map</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:22%"><col style="width:36%"><col style="width:42%"></colgroup><tr><th>Step</th><th>Current pain</th><th>Recommended setup</th></tr><tr><td>Intake</td><td>Details arrive through texts and email.</td><td>Use one request form and one lead tracker.</td></tr><tr><td>Sort</td><td>Owner has to remember package and next step.</td><td>Use package/status columns and missing-info prompts.</td></tr><tr><td>Draft</td><td>Replies and quotes are rewritten every time.</td><td>Use reusable templates and prompt pack.</td></tr><tr><td>Track</td><td>Follow-ups get missed.</td><td>Use next-action and due-date dashboard.</td></tr><tr><td>Handoff</td><td>Delivery wording changes every job.</td><td>Use delivery email template with first action and upgrade path.</td></tr></table><h2>Prompt pack starter</h2><div class="note"><b>Missing-info prompt:</b> Turn this customer request into a short missing-information checklist. Separate facts, assumptions, and questions. Keep it friendly and direct.</div><div class="note"><b>Quote draft prompt:</b> Draft a quote reply using the service, customer goal, included items, not-included items, price range, timing, and next step.</div><div class="note"><b>Delivery prompt:</b> Write a customer handoff email summarizing the deliverable, first action, missing information, and optional next package.</div><h2>Dashboard fields</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:32%"><col style="width:68%"></colgroup><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr><tr><td>Lead status</td><td>New, Need Info, Quoted, Approved, In Build, Delivered.</td></tr><tr><td>Package</td><td>Problem Snapshot, Project Packet, AI Workflow, etc.</td></tr><tr><td>Next action</td><td>Owner knows what to do next.</td></tr><tr><td>Due date</td><td>Prevents stuck work.</td></tr><tr><td>Follow-up date</td><td>Prevents dead leads.</td></tr></table><p class="small">Highway 38 Solutions - Big problems. Clear plans. Hypothetical sample deliverable.</p></body></html>